---
import BaseHead from '../components/BaseHead.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
	<head>
		<BaseHead title="FastCron IP addresses list" description="See all IP addresses that FastCron uses to process your cronjob" />
		<title></title>
	</head>
	<body>
		<Header />

		<section class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-900">
			<div class="py-8 px-4 mx-auto max-w-screen-xl sm:py-16 lg:px-6">
				<div class="format lg:format-lg mx-auto">
					<h1>FastCron IP addresses list</h1>
	
					<p>We are using several servers to process your cronjobs.</p>
					<p>Here are our IP addresses:</p>
					<pre class="p-2 border bg-secondary bg-opacity-10">64.225.48.218
134.209.39.102
143.198.114.177
138.197.75.231
159.223.144.10
143.244.166.206
147.182.184.93
</pre>
	
					<p>Our IPv6 addresses:</p>
	
					<pre class="p-2 border bg-secondary bg-opacity-10">2604:a880:800:10::7cf:5001
2604:a880:800:10::80b:e001
2604:a880:400:d0::98:3001
2604:a880:800:10::a78:c001
2604:a880:400:d0::33:f001
2604:a880:400:d0::25cb:b001
2604:a880:400:d0::18f1:f001
</pre>
	
					<p>Please make sure that we can reach your cronjob URLs from these IP addresses.</p>
	
					<p>
						If you want to receive email notifications when we update our IP addresses,
						please log in to FastCron,
						visit Account &gt; Profile,
						check the box "Receive email notifications about FastCron IP change".
					</p>
	
					<p>
						You can fetch our IP list at
						<a href="/ip.txt" target="_blank">https://www.fastcron.com/ip.txt</a>
						(all IP),
	
						<a href="/ipv4.txt" target="_blank">https://www.fastcron.com/ipv4.txt</a>
						(IPv4 only),
						<a href="/ipv6.txt" target="_blank">https://www.fastcron.com/ipv6.txt</a>
						(IPv6 only).
					</p>
				</div>
			</div>
